{
  "texts": [
    "It is our impression that especially the SR Research Experiment Builder and Data Viewer software bundle is a popular tool among reading researchers.",
    "EyeMap (Tang et al., 2012; see also Hegarty-Kelly, 2020) is an open-source tool for the analysis of reading data, and the EyeTrack, EyeDoctor and EyeDry tools from the university of Amherst (Abbott, 2011, see https://websites.umass.edu/ eyelab/software/) offer an environment for conducting measurements, visually inspecting and analyzing reading data.",
    "Furthermore, there is the popEye toolbox for the R environment (Schroeder, 2019 (Schroeder,, 2022)) and eyekit for Python (Carr, 2023).",
    "The cleaning of fixation data for reading analyses, such as removing fixations that are too short, is examined by Eskenazi (2024).",
    "Tools for comparing scanpaths during reading are available (von der Malsburg & Vasishth, 2011; Ma et al., 2023)."
  ]
}